                    "company": "University of Colorado Boulder",
                    "description": "\u201cYou may pump a simulated balloon and with every pump you win $1. At some point the balloon wil pop and you lose all your money. How often would you like to pump the balloon?\u201d.\n\nThis description is part of the \u2018balloon analogue risk task\u2019. This task was developed by psychologists and has had many success in predicting risky health behaviors. As part of my postdoctoral training I worked on a reconfiguration of this game for economists as to test whether we could use this task to predict financial decision-making. \nFurthermore I strengthened my expertise in neuroimaging experiments by collaborating with a diverse set of researchers which backgrounds stem from neuroscience, psychology and computer science.",
