                    "description": "Which gamble would you choose? \nGamble A: you win $10 if the coin tosses head and $0 if it lands tails\nGamble B: I will give you $5 for sure\n\nFrom such lotteries I\u2019m able to assess your willingness to take risks and it potentially allows me to predict how you make financial decisions in your daily life. Not surprisingly this latter goal is very challenging as contexts, many social influences and your emotions and mood all play a role when you make a decision in real-life. \nDuring my PhD research I focused on the development of several laboratory risk tasks in order to better characterise individuals\u2019 preferences for risk. \nTo achieve this goal, I combined insights from economics, psychology and neuroscience.",
